==Korean==
===Noun===
'''갈매기''' (''galmaegi'')
# [[gull]], [[seagull]], cf. Japanese [[カモメ]] (''kamome'') 

====Alternative spellings====
* 갈머기 (''galmeogi'') (obsolete)
* 갈며기 (''galmyeogi'') (obsolete)
* 갈멱이 (''galmyeogI'') (obsolete), cf. [[멱]] (''myeog'') [[dip]]ping, [[bathing]]
* 갈미 (''galmi'') (obsolete)

====Related terms====
* [[머구리]] (''meoguri'') (obsolete) [[frog]], cf. Japanese [[潜り]] ([[もぐり]], ''moguri'') [[diver]] 
* [[멱]] (''myeog, myeok'', [[沐]], [[浴]]) [[dip]]ping, [[bathing]] (in waters)
* [[미역]] (''miyeog, miyeok'', [[沐]], [[浴]]) [[dip]]ping, [[bathing]] (in waters)
* [[무자맥질]] (''mujamaegjil, -maekjil'', [[潛]], [[潜]]) [[dip]]ping, [[diving]], [[ducking]], cf. Dutch [[duiken]], German [[ducken]], [[tauchen]]  

====See also====
* [[목]] (''mog, mok'') [[neck]]
* [[목]] ([[沐]], ''mog, mok'') To wash hair (perhaps by bending down the neck, lowering the head, into water) 
; Analogy
* [[멱]] (''myeog, myeok'') [[front]] [[neck]], [[throat]]. (The long neck is dramatically bent down and plunged into water at first or at least when [[waterfowl]]s dive.)
* [[멱]] (''myeog, myeok'') ([[沐]]) [[dipping]], [[bathing]] (in waters)  

